President Trump held a press conference to announce new actions aimed at increasing transparency in the healthcare industry. The president discussed the importance of price transparency and the impact it will have on consumers. He announced that hospitals will be required to publish prices publicly online for everyone to see and compare, and health insurance providers will be required to disclose their pricing information to consumers. The president emphasized that these actions will give patients more control over their healthcare decisions and help lower costs. He also mentioned other healthcare initiatives, such as reducing the price of prescription drugs and expanding affordable alternatives to Obamacare plans. The president criticized the ongoing impeachment hearings, accusing Democrats of denying Republicans due process and impeding their ability to ask questions. He defended his right to freedom of speech and denied that his tweets and words were intimidating. The press conference ended with the president expressing his dissatisfaction with the media's coverage of his statements and calling for more honest reporting.